<br>
Each class needs something to make them stand out. I mean...they need to be able to do a certain job better than anyone else....thats why there are different classes...correct?  <br>
<br>
Rangers...traditionally....are good with archery.  Cong them on actually being good at it.  <br>
<br>
Wizards nuke.  Simple enough...I think its only right that they can nuke way better than mages.<br>
<br>
Clerics heal.  Is is unfair that they can heal my pet better than I can?  Nope.<br>
<br>
Chanters mesmerize...charm...etc.<br>
<br>
See where I'm going with this?<br>
<br>
The only class I really have a problem with...(and this is NOT a rant...just an observation)...is druids.  They are supposed to be the jack of all trades....meaning they can do pretty much some of all of it...yet not as well as the &quot;primary&quot; class for that ability.  I guess they have gotten their buffs because they complained loud enough and long enough...and there were enough of them to do so...so cong them for it.  They nuke on par with us....they are the second best healers in game....etc.  I guess that if the others classes outpace them in PoP...then thats ok...everything will even out.  But..I degress...<br>
<br>
My point is...if a ranger can do 200+dps with archery....then that falls in line with pretty much any &quot;fantasy world&quot; rules in my eyes.  <br>
<br>
Warriors are the ones that should REALLY be complaining.  I mean...what can they do that a pally and sk cannot...other than dual wield?  I mean..on average..they might have a few more hp...but they need a class defining ability.  <br>
<br>
Mages?  We are very good damage dealers.  We summon the best pets in all of Norrath....we nuke well...and we can provide other classes with an alternate means of mana.  I feel that if FB was putting out enough damage to make it worth getting....AND we actually got some new summon spells that were on par with current encounters....then we wouldn't have too much left to complain about...except for the fact that....when sitting in the bazaar...we still look pretty much the same as wizards and chanters....<br>
<br>
On a side note...(sorry to hijack here)...since we are discussing classes....why not make a new one?  The Sorcerer?  Hybrid between mage and melee?  I mean...there are rangers..(druids/melee)...sk's...(necro/melee)...pallies..(cleric/melee)...<br>
<br>
Nah...maybe not....<br>
<br>
Llassar Wurmburner<br>
Mage of the 55th Circle<br>
<br>
P.S.  I know whats coming next.  Someone is gonna reply that I'm only level 55...and don't know the first thing about the end game..OR Frenzied Burnout (I know...because its happened before..).  So...to go ahead and respond to that....I don't see too many mages shooting a bow and arrow either.  <br>
